narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, not too much work and you learn a lot. The essays take a lot of care.
Definitely take it if you want to learn more about West African Jihad and so many other things about Islam and Africa.

It's a course about the penetration of Islam into sub-Saharan Africa. It's about the jihad movements that were responsible for the initial spread of Islam in the region. The class also looks at Sufi/pacifist movements that pushed back against jihadist currents.
